{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry includes Erlin1/2 (also known as SPFH1/2) from animals and their homologues from plants. Mammalian Erlin1 and Erlin2 form a complex that mediates the endoplasmic reticulum-associated degradation (ERAD) of inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptors (IP3Rs) such as ITPR1 [[cite:PUB00078357], [cite:PUB00078358], [cite:PUB00078359]]. The Erlin1/2 complex may recruit RNF170 (an E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase) to activated IP(3) receptors where it mediates IP(3) receptor ubiquitination [[cite:PUB00078360]].</p>\n\n<p>Interestingly, C. elegans erlin homologue, ERL-1, does not play an essential role in the endoplasmic reticulum-associated degradation (ERAD) of inositol 1,4,5-triphosphate receptors (IP3Rs) [[cite:PUB00093085]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR15351" "ERLIN (ER LIPID RAFT ASSOCIATED PROTEIN) HOMOLOG"}, "cdd" {"cd03406" "Uncharacterized family; SPFH (stomatin, prohibitin, flotillin, and HflK/C) superfamily"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Erlin1/2", "short" "Erlin1/2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1178, "taxa" 4642, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3809, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3808, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2292}, "pathways" 10}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR033294", :literature {"PUB00078357" {"URL" nil, "issue" "16", "authors" ["Pearce MM" "Wormer DB" "Wilkens S" "Wojcikiewicz RJ."], "ISO_journal" "J. Biol. Chem.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1074/jbc.M809801200", "medline_journal" "J Biol Chem", "title" "An endoplasmic reticulum (ER) membrane complex composed of SPFH1 and SPFH2 mediates the ER-associated degradation of inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptors.", "year" 2009, "raw_pages" "10433-45", "volume" "284", "ISBN" 